## Description {#details}

This file defines common analysis utilities used by the ObjC ARC Optimizer.

ARC stands for Automatic Reference Counting and is a system for managing reference counts for objects in Objective C.

WARNING: This file knows about certain library functions. It recognizes them by name, and hardwires knowledge of their semantics.

WARNING: This file knows about how certain Objective-C library functions are used. Naive LLVM IR transformations which would otherwise be behavior-preserving may break these assumptions.

<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The RCIdentity root of a value \\p V is a dominating value U for which</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><Highlight kind="comment">/// retaining or releasing U is equivalent to retaining or releasing V. In other</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><Highlight kind="comment">/// We use this in the ARC optimizer to make it easier to match up ARC</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operations by always mapping ARC operations to RCIdentityRoots instead of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pointers themselves.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The two ways that we see RCIdentical values in ObjC are via:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><Highlight kind="comment">///   1 PointerCasts</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><Highlight kind="comment">///   2 Forwarding Calls that return their argument verbatim.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Thus this function strips off pointer casts and forwarding calls. &#42;NOTE&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This implies that two RCIdentical values must alias.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
